{"id":"project-LICHEN-gqwn","title":"oscore_unprotect_response ignores PIV in OSCORE option (RFC 8613 violation)","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/oscore/oscore.c
Lines: 1882-1884

The oscore_unprotect_response function explicitly ignores the OSCORE option:
```c
(void)oscore_opt;
(void)oscore_opt_len;
```

Per RFC 8613 Section 8.4, OSCORE responses MAY include a Partial IV in the OSCORE option. When present, this PIV should be used for nonce computation instead of the request PIV.

This is a protocol compliance issue:
1. Responses with PIV in option will fail decryption
2. The implementation cannot interoperate with servers that include response PIV
3. The nonce may be computed incorrectly

The function signature accepts oscore_opt but then discards it without parsing.

Fix: Parse the OSCORE option and use response PIV for nonce if present:
```c
struct oscore_option resp_opt;
if (oscore_opt_len > 0) {
    ret = oscore_option_parse(oscore_opt, oscore_opt_len, &resp_opt);
    if (ret != OSCORE_OK) return ret;
    if (resp_opt.has_piv && resp_opt.piv_len > 0) {
        // Use response PIV for nonce instead of request PIV
        compute_nonce(..., resp_opt.piv, resp_opt.piv_len, ...);
    }
}
